    "data": {
      "title": "invoice numbers",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": true,
      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "\nconst template = readline();\nconst increment = parseInt(readline());\n\n\n\nconst match = template.match(/\\d+$/gi)\n\nvar result = \"INVALID\"\n\nif (match) {\n    const root = match[0];\n    const text = template.substr(0, template.length - root.length);\n    const newCount = parseInt(root) + increment;\n    const newCountText = newCount.toString();\n\n    if (newCountText.length <= root.length) {\n        result = text + '0'.repeat(root.length - newCountText.length) + newCount\n    }\n    else\n        result = \"OUT OF RANGE\"\n}\nconsole.log(result)",
      "statement": "You must output the next invoice number, based on a [[template]] and an [[increment]].\n\nThe template is a string that must end with a number. If it's possible you must add the [[increment]] to this number.\n\n<<Example>>:  \n[[template]] {{INVOICE-0040}}\n[[increment]] {{8}}\n<<Output>> {{INVOICE-0048}}\n\n[[template]] can be invalid if it doesn't end with a number. In this case output must be <<INVALID>>\n\nIf the next invoice number has more digits than the template, you must output <<OUT OF RANGE>> (e.g. if [[template]] is {{SI-00}} and the [[increment]] is {{100}}, {{SI-100}} is not a valid answer).",
